lerado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"121","text":"CAR aplanado o plano → signo de agotamiento del eje HPA (burnout neuroendocrino)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"121","text":"Fibromialgia con cortisol alterado → evaluar siempre sueño y carga alostática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"121","text":"NLRP3-ASC: blanco terapéutico emergente en neurodegeneración relacionada con estrés","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"121","text":"Resistencia a cortisol: no es igual que cortisol bajo → la respuesta inflamatoria persiste","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"1. Nicolaides NC et al. The Hypothalamic-Pituitary-Adrenal Axis: The Actions of the Central Stress System During Homeostasis and Pathology. Physiology. 2020.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"2. Joëls M, Baram TZ. The neuro-symphony of stress. Nat Rev Neurosci. 2009;10(6):459-66.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"3. McEwen BS. Neurobiological and systemic effects of chronic stress. Chronic Stress. 2017;1.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"129","text":"4. Bhagya V et al. Chronic unpredictable stress-induced depressive behaviors in rodents. Behav Brain Res. 2021.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"129","text":"5. Staufenbiel SM et al. Hair cortisol, stress exposure, and mental health in humans. Psychoneuroendocrinology. 2013;38(8):1220-35.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"129","text":"6. Hardy MP et al. Stress hormone and male reproductive function. Cell Tissue Res. 2005;322(1):147-53.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"129","text":"7. Pervanidou P, Chrousos GP. Metabolic consequences of stress during childhood and adolescence. Metabolism. 2012;61(5):611-9.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"129","text":"8. Bhatt S et al. Cortisol levels and Alzh